gist’s account of what has arguably been one of the most sweeping events in the history of brain research—the highly contested effort to consider the adult brain in embryogenetic terms. A careful analysis of the disproving of an established truth, it reveals the turmoil that such a disruption brings about and the emergence of new possibilities of thinking and knowing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBrainxResearchxHistory. 0aDevelopmental neurobiology. 0aNeuroplasticity. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aadult brain.  abrain research.  abrain science.  acellular plasticity of the brain.  acentral nervous system.  adevelopmental neurobiology.  aembryogenetic processes in the adult brain.  aevolution.  ahistory of brain science.  ahistory of medicine.  ahuman brain.  alifelong development.  amature brain development.  amedical anthropology.  anervous system.  aneurobiology.  aneurology.  aneuronal research.  aneuroplasticity.  aneuroscience research.  aplasticity of human brain.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028812640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096317740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963177423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963177/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY